By Raji Rasak Badagry – The police on Tuesday arraigned  three applicants in a Badagry Chief Magistrates’ Court, for allegedly being in possession India hemp. The police also charged Taiwo Samuel,32; Sunday Salako,21 and Matthew
Aworonsu, 39, whose addresses were not given with  breach of peace . The Police Counsel, Sgt. Ayodele Adeosun, told the court that the
defendants committed the offence on April 25, at about 4 p.m., at Apasa
Quarters, Ajido, Badagry, Lagos. Adeosun said the offence contravened the provisions of sections 168
and 330 of Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015 as amended,” he said. The defendants, however, pleaded not guilty to the charge. Chief Magistrate, Patrick Adekomaya admitted the defendants to bail
in the sum of N100, 000 each with one surety each in like sum. Adekomaya adjourned the case until May 28, for hearing.